{
  "stem": "19895.2",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And as European history goes, which I don't think we should go too deep into it, there was anti-Semitism from the Middle Ages all the way to leading up to the Nazi times.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And Hungary, indeed, was very much part of that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Hungarian Jewish population, relatively speaking to the size of the country, was a large Jewish community.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Hungarian Jews were close to 6%, 7% of the total population of the country and, and had a very strong influence on the culture and the cultural life of Hungary.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they were successful in, in, in many areas of daily life, business, and, and, and culture, and theater, and newspapers, and writings, and so forth.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And it was not taken very well by the other people who always started to push back and, and, and curtail the achievements of the Jews.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Also, for example, some of the so-called anti-Jewish laws-- and there were several of them-- started to push back the number of admissions to the universities.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The numerus clausus, closure on the number of how many Jewish people can be admitted to universities were every three, four years were pushed back and pushed back further and, and, and minimized.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Why those people who were in universities, they were constantly attacked by very rightist movements, young students of their own classes.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And there are documented atrocities against--",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Jewish school people.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I do know it also from a, from a first hand experience in my, in my year when I was, I think, 12 or going on 13 when our school building on [INAUDIBLE] street, the Budapest Jewish gymnasium school, was attacked physically by a stone and brick-throwing group of people.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was in a gymnastic class at the time.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
